<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,378,585]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,450,477]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Distribution.</emphasis>
This is the first record from 
<collectingCountry box="[681,832,451,477]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1283,451,477]" name="Malta" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Malta</collectingCountry>
(as “Melita”, by 
<typeStatus box="[186,289,487,513]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">lectotype</typeStatus>
des. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clausen, P. J." box="[346,559,487,513]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" pagination="141 - 142" refId="ref26929" refString="Clausen, P. J. (1979) Lectotype designation of Ochthera schembrii Rondani (Diptera: Ephydridae) and resulting synonomies. Entomological News, 90, 141 - 142." type="journal article" year="1979">Clausen 1979: 141</bibRefCitation>
). It is widespread in the Palaearctic Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[1056,1143,487,513]" name="Algeria" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, Azores, 
<collectingCountry box="[1245,1344,487,513]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, Canary Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[246,316,523,549]" name="Egypt" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[329,480,523,549]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
, 
